          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>&lt;div id="github-card"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>JavaScript</h3>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>import &#123;getRepoStats, renderRepoCard&#125; from 'github-repo-stats-card'

// Get repository data
const stats = await getRepoStats('vuejs/vue')

// Render the card with the obtained data
renderRepoCard('#github-card', stats)

// With authentication token
const statsWithToken = await getRepoStats('vuejs/vue', 'ghp_your_token_here')
renderRepoCard('#github-card', statsWithToken)</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>TypeScript</h3>
          <p>The package includes full TypeScript support with defined types:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>import &#123;getRepoStats, renderRepoCard, RepoStats&#125; from 'github-repo-stats-card'

// Get typed data
const stats: RepoStats = await getRepoStats('vuejs/vue')
console.log(stats.stargazersCount) // number
console.log(stats.languages) // Record&lt;string, number&gt;

// Render with typed data
renderRepoCard('#github-card', stats)</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è Important Security Note</h4>
            <p><strong>getRepoStats</strong> should always be used on the server side to avoid exposing the token to the client.</p>
            <p><strong>renderRepoCard</strong> can be safely used on the client or server side.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="api" class="docs-section">
          <h2>API Reference</h2>
          
          <h3>getRepoStats(repoName, githubAuthToken?)</h3>
          <p>Gets only repository data without manipulating the DOM.</p>
          
